Obama Says He’s ‘Confident’ of Debt Compromise

-- B y   K a t e   A n d e r s e n   B r o w e r   a n d   M a r g a r e t   T a l e v
-- 
2011-07-26T01:15:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-26/obama-says-he-s-confident-of-debt-compromise.html
President  Barack Obama  said he
remains confident the current stalemate over raising the
nation’s debt ceiling still can be resolved if both sides
compromise.  Obama, in an address from the White House, warned of dire
economic consequences if Congress and the administration don’t
reach an agreement by the Aug. 2 deadline set by the Treasury
Department.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kate Andersen Brower in Washington at 
